# StackSift Architecture Guardrails

## Backend
- Use .NET 10 and C# 13 features (Primary Constructors, Collection Expressions).
- Follow Clean Architecture strictly: Api → Infrastructure → Application → Domain.
- No cross-layer violations: Domain must never reference Infrastructure.
- Use FluentValidation for all input validation.
- Use MediatR for CQRS (Commands/Queries must be in Application layer).
- Use Entity Framework Core with PostgreSQL (with pgvector for semantic search).
- Controllers must be thin — delegate all logic to MediatR handlers.

## Frontend
- Use Next.js 15+ App Router only. No Pages Router.
- TypeScript strict mode is mandatory (`"strict": true` in tsconfig).
- Use Tailwind CSS for styling. No inline styles or CSS modules unless justified.
- Use TanStack Query v5 for all server-state management.
- Use Zod for all runtime schema validation (API responses, forms).
- No `any` types — enforce via ESLint rule `@typescript-eslint/no-explicit-any`.

## Git
- Enforce Conventional Commits: feat:, fix:, docs:, chore:, refactor:, test:, ci:
- Branch naming: feature/, fix/, docs/, chore/
- All PRs must reference a GitHub Issue.
- No direct commits to `main`.

## Documentation
- Maintain a "doc-first" approach: every feature starts with docs/ai-log.md entry.
- Every new API endpoint must be documented in OpenAPI (Swagger).
- Every significant AI-assisted session must be logged in docs/ai-log.md.
- README must always reflect the current architecture and running instructions.

## Security
- No secrets in code. Use environment variables and Docker secrets.
- Keycloak is the sole Identity Provider — no mock auth, no local JWT generation.
- All API endpoints must be protected (except explicitly public ones).
